through an alternative
description

00:30:57.940 --> 00:31:01.700
of what light does to atoms
using the dressed atom picture,

00:31:01.700 --> 00:31:03.550
and in the dressed
atom picture, we

00:31:03.550 --> 00:31:06.040
will very naturally
understand why

00:31:06.040 --> 00:31:09.180
now blue-detuned light
provides cooling.

00:31:09.180 --> 00:31:11.770
But right now, for you,
this should be a mystery,

00:31:11.770 --> 00:31:14.260
but it should be something
where you say, hey,

00:31:14.260 --> 00:31:17.000
still something
qualitative is missing

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:19.175
in our understanding
of light forces.

00:31:21.860 --> 00:31:25.240
OK, I will not be
able to explain

00:31:25.240 --> 00:31:28.200
it [? physically ?] to you.

00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:30.350
I first have to introduce
the dressed atom picture,

00:31:30.350 --> 00:31:33.780
and I will do that it
in 10 minutes or so.

00:31:33.780 --> 00:31:37.190
But what I want to do
here is if I'm telling you

00:31:37.190 --> 00:31:40.350
something goes terribly
wrong and we completely

00:31:40.350 --> 00:31:43.690
miss even the sign of the
force, blue-detuned light is now

00:31:43.690 --> 00:31:45.710
cooling, not red-detuned
light, I at least

00:31:45.710 --> 00:31:48.370
want to tell you
what went wrong.

00:31:48.370 --> 00:31:52.720
Because haven't we done
an almost exact discussion

00:31:52.720 --> 00:31:54.380
of light forces?

00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:57.484
We used the gradient of d dot e.

00:31:57.484 --> 00:32:01.090
We used for d the steady state
solution of the optical Bloch

00:32:01.090 --> 00:32:01.660
equations.

00:32:01.660 --> 00:32:05.170
Haven't we done
everything right?

00:32:05.170 --> 00:32:09.790
Well, we did approximations.

00:32:09.790 --> 00:32:13.910
And what happens is,
and this is the reason

00:32:13.910 --> 00:32:18.240
for those qualitatively
different things, that we

00:32:18.240 --> 00:32:23.980
should, in order to get
those effects, not use,

00:32:23.980 --> 00:32:27.960
for the dipole moment, for the
off-diagonal matrix elements

00:32:27.960 --> 00:32:30.930
of the density matrix,
the steady state solution

00:32:30.930 --> 00:32:33.070
for optical Bloch vector.

00:32:33.070 --> 00:32:37.910
We have to acknowledge that
it always takes a finite time

00:32:37.910 --> 00:32:41.420
to reach steady state.

00:32:41.420 --> 00:32:46.090
For instance, if he takes, let's
say, a spontaneous emission

00:32:46.090 --> 00:32:49.730
time, if the atom goes
through a standing wave,

00:32:49.730 --> 00:32:52.830
it goes from high
intensity to low intensity,

00:32:52.830 --> 00:32:55.630
it takes about one
spontaneous emission time.

00:32:55.630 --> 00:32:57.850
When you are highly
excited, but now you

00:32:57.850 --> 00:33:00.120
go through a node of
the standing wave,

00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:02.030
the steady state
solution is [INAUDIBLE].

00:33:02.030 --> 00:33:04.450
At the node of the standing
wave, there is no light.

00:33:04.450 --> 00:33:06.090
The steady state
solution with no light

00:33:06.090 --> 00:33:07.960
is you better go back
to the ground state,

00:33:07.960 --> 00:33:10.200
but that takes
something on the order

00:33:10.200 --> 00:33:12.480
of the spontaneous
emission time.

00:33:12.480 --> 00:33:15.680
So therefore, when I
am excited because I'm

00:33:15.680 --> 00:33:18.110
in the middle of the
[? pied ?] laser beam

00:33:18.110 --> 00:33:20.820
and I go fast into
the dark region,

00:33:20.820 --> 00:33:23.060
I'm still excited because
I didn't have time

00:33:23.060 --> 00:33:25.310
to get rid of my excitation.

00:33:25.310 --> 00:33:29.340
In other words, the
internal degree of freedom,

00:33:29.340 --> 00:33:32.040
the population of
grounded excited state,

00:33:32.040 --> 00:33:35.580
will lag behind the
steady state solution

00:33:35.580 --> 00:33:39.940
by a lag time which is a
spontaneous emission time.

00:33:39.940 --> 00:33:43.730
And that would mean if I
multiply with the velocity,

00:33:43.730 --> 00:33:46.820
it's pretty much that there
is a spacial displacement.

00:33:53.360 --> 00:33:59.770
I'm always a certain distance
away from the steady state

00:33:59.770 --> 00:34:01.200
solution.

00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:09.880
And actually, this point,
to introduce the lag time,

00:34:09.880 --> 00:34:13.130
we with do it in a
wonderful, physical way when

00:34:13.130 --> 00:34:14.830
we have the dressed
atom picture,

00:34:14.830 --> 00:34:18.620
but it can be done with
optical Bloch equation.

00:34:18.620 --> 00:34:21.770
It's just a real pain because
the optical Bloch equation

00:34:21.770 --> 00:34:24.469
is sort of like a
matrix the equation.

00:34:24.469 --> 00:34:27.239
It's completely
obscure, how it is done,

00:34:27.239 --> 00:34:29.480
but in order that you
convince yourself,

00:34:29.480 --> 00:34:33.580
I posted the original paper
from Gordon and Ashkin

00:34:33.580 --> 00:34:34.900
where this was done.

00:34:34.900 --> 00:34:36.080
You read the math.

00:34:36.080 --> 00:34:37.710
You understand the
result, but you

00:34:37.710 --> 00:34:40.710
don't understand the derivation,
the physical picture behind it.

00:34:40.710 --> 00:34:44.300
The dressed atom picture will
give us a lucid explanation

00:34:44.300 --> 00:34:47.340
for exactly what a
lag time does and why

00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:50.159
this results in colling.

00:34:50.159 --> 00:34:53.645
But anyway, this is the
physics we have done wrong.

00:34:53.645 --> 00:34:55.570
At low power, it's OK.

00:34:55.570 --> 00:34:58.620
At high power, we really
have to take care of effect.

00:35:01.790 --> 00:35:05.210
And if we would take care
of effect-- And as I said,

00:35:05.210 --> 00:35:07.320
we don't need the
dressed atom picture,

00:35:07.320 --> 00:35:09.960
we can fully do it within the
framework of the optical Bloch

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:12.120
equation, but it's messy.

00:35:12.120 --> 00:35:15.710
--we would actually get out, and
you see that in the references,

00:35:15.710 --> 00:35:19.230
the result that the friction
coefficient in a standing wave

00:35:19.230 --> 00:35:23.820
at weak power is exactly two
times the friction coefficient

00:35:23.820 --> 00:35:29.880
for a travelling wave, and
that justifies that we describe

00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:33.120
molasses by the spontaneous
light force of two travelling

00:35:33.120 --> 00:35:36.070
waves, completely ignoring
the standing wave.

00:35:36.070 --> 00:35:39.250
But the same treatment of
the optical Bloch equation

00:35:39.250 --> 00:35:41.690
will then, eventually,
give us the result

00:35:41.690 --> 00:35:45.810
that alpha changes
sign at high intensity.

00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:48.400
But as I said, I
want to describe

00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:51.460
that after we have introduced
the dressed atom picture.

00:35:54.640 --> 00:35:57.180
Questions?

00:35:57.180 --> 00:36:00.040
OK, we have done molasses
in one dimension.

00:36:00.040 --> 00:36:01.840
We have done beam slowing.

00:36:01.840 --> 00:36:04.160
We just did a short
discussion about molasses

00:36:04.160 --> 00:36:06.140
in arbitrary dimensions.

00:36:06.140 --> 00:36:08.010
The one technique
which is missing now

00:36:08.010 --> 00:36:09.890
is the magneto-optic trap.

00:36:12.920 --> 00:36:22.430
Let me just spend five
minutes to discuss

00:36:22.430 --> 00:36:25.650
the background behind
the magneto-optic trap

00:36:25.650 --> 00:36:29.610
because for many of you,
I think you were just

00:36:29.610 --> 00:36:32.910
born when the magneto-optic
trap was invented.

00:36:32.910 --> 00:36:39.880
Well, I joined
the field in 1990,

00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:43.620
and that was three years
after the magneto-optic trap

00:36:43.620 --> 00:36:45.520
has been invented.

00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:52.490
And many people say if there is
one most singular development

00:36:52.490 --> 00:36:54.420
in laser cooling and
such, it's molasses

00:36:54.420 --> 00:36:56.860
and the magneto-optical trap.

00:36:56.860 --> 00:37:00.200
So let me tell you why,
the magneto-optical trap,

00:37:00.200 --> 00:37:03.760
you shouldn't take
it for granted.

00:37:03.760 --> 00:37:11.610
It was actually in
1983 that Ashkin--

00:37:11.610 --> 00:37:12.610
Was it Gordon or Ashkin?

00:37:12.610 --> 00:37:14.130
I think Ashkin, Art Ashkin.

00:37:14.130 --> 00:37:17.670
--that he presented an
Optical Earnshaw theorem,

00:37:17.670 --> 00:37:20.970
and it is nicely described
in Bill Phillips' Varenna

00:37:20.970 --> 00:37:23.670
notes which I have
posted on the website.

00:37:23.670 --> 00:37:30.530
And it's pretty much a proof
that you cannot build a trap

00:37:30.530 --> 00:37:32.720
using the spontaneous
light force.

00:37:32.720 --> 00:37:35.110
So in other words,
this is a proof

00:37:35.110 --> 00:37:38.881
which people took
as a correct proof

00:37:38.881 --> 00:37:40.630
that something like
the magneto-optic trap

00:37:40.630 --> 00:37:42.750
could not exist.

00:37:42.750 --> 00:37:45.200
So what this is proof like?

00:37:45.200 --> 00:37:47.870
Well, and that
sort of teaches you

00:37:47.870 --> 00:37:52.115
what was the mental concept
or the mental barrier people

00:37:52.115 --> 00:37:54.180
had to break through
before they invented

00:37:54.180 --> 00:37:55.580
the magneto-optic trap.

00:37:55.580 --> 00:37:57.280
The proof is the following.

00:37:57.280 --> 00:38:02.400
If you think that you
have beams-- I mean,

00:38:02.400 --> 00:38:06.600
a model for the spontaneous
light force is you have photons

00:38:06.600 --> 00:38:09.900
and the photons are
sand blasting the atom.

00:38:09.900 --> 00:38:12.580
Each photon is like
a grain of sand,

00:38:12.580 --> 00:38:16.040
and the atom is in scattering
descent in all directions.

00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:18.470
You can really make this
completely classical picture

00:38:18.470 --> 00:38:19.890
of the spontaneous light force.

00:38:22.570 --> 00:38:23.070
Almost.

00:38:27.650 --> 00:38:31.310
If you do with that you would
say the spontaneous light force

00:38:31.310 --> 00:38:35.840
is proportional to
the stream of photons

00:38:35.840 --> 00:38:39.480
which is described by
the Poynting vector.

00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:42.480
But now, you have
in electromagnetism

00:38:42.480 --> 00:38:47.460
a continuity equation which says
the divergence of the Poynting

00:38:47.460 --> 00:38:52.360
vector plus the change of energy
density in a certain volume

00:38:52.360 --> 00:38:55.160
has to be 0.

00:38:55.160 --> 00:38:57.060
So if you are in
steady state-- If you

00:38:57.060 --> 00:38:58.790
have an arrangement
of laser beams

00:38:58.790 --> 00:39:03.500
and the energy density of
the electromagnetic field

00:39:03.500 --> 00:39:06.260
is at steady state,
that tells you

00:39:06.260 --> 00:39:10.620
that the divergence of the
Poynting vector has to be 0.

00:39:10.620 --> 00:39:13.340
Well, if the divergence
of the Poynting vector

00:39:13.340 --> 00:39:15.806
is 0, using this
equation that says

00:39:15.806 --> 00:39:17.680
the divergence of the
spontaneous light force

00:39:17.680 --> 00:39:19.750
has to be 0.

00:39:19.750 --> 00:39:21.830
But if the divergence
of the force

00:39:21.830 --> 00:39:25.610
has to be 0, that means you
can not have a force which

00:39:25.610 --> 00:39:29.540
is inward from all directions
because such a force,

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:31.670
a trap needs a force
which is inward.

00:39:31.670 --> 00:39:34.255
A trap requires a
negative divergence.

00:39:38.506 --> 00:39:43.520
Do you see the wrong
assumption in this proof,

00:39:43.520 --> 00:39:46.190
or did I convince you that
the magneto-optic trap is not

00:39:46.190 --> 00:39:52.750
possible because this
proof would say you can not

00:39:52.750 --> 00:39:55.270
make a trap out of the
spontaneous light force?

00:40:00.080 --> 00:40:02.806
AUDIENCE: Well, you through out
the change in energy density,

00:40:02.806 --> 00:40:04.090
so that's--

00:40:04.090 --> 00:40:07.200
PROFESSOR: But that's
OK because if you switch

00:40:07.200 --> 00:40:12.470
on a laser beam, light
travels at the speed of light,

00:40:12.470 --> 00:40:16.380
and in 10 to the minus 10
seconds, in picoseconds,

00:40:16.380 --> 00:40:18.200
you reach steady state.

00:40:18.200 --> 00:40:20.180
And you know when
you operate the MOT,

00:40:20.180 --> 00:40:24.400
you're not switching on and
off your lasers at picoseconds.

00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:27.072
It's not that.

00:40:27.072 --> 00:40:27.780
Yes, [INAUDIBLE].

00:40:27.780 --> 00:40:30.636
AUDIENCE: --the
spacial variation of c.

00:40:30.636 --> 00:40:34.450
PROFESSOR: Yes, exactly.

00:40:34.450 --> 00:40:39.220
The force is not just
proportional to the Poynting

00:40:39.220 --> 00:40:39.930
vector.

00:40:39.930 --> 00:40:45.020
This would be true if
I had grains of sand,

00:40:45.020 --> 00:40:49.000
but photons have to fill
a resonance condition.

00:40:49.000 --> 00:40:54.860
You can maybe
assume I'm an atom,

00:40:54.860 --> 00:40:59.100
but I have an spatially varying
magnetic field around me.

00:40:59.100 --> 00:41:02.990
At the one magnetic
field, I feel the force

00:41:02.990 --> 00:41:05.060
of the laser beam
because I am resonant.

00:41:05.060 --> 00:41:07.250
At another magnetic
field, the laser beam

00:41:07.250 --> 00:41:10.950
just goes through me because
I'm not in resonance.

00:41:10.950 --> 00:41:12.880
So therefore, the
proportionality

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:14.950
between the Poynting
vector of the laser

00:41:14.950 --> 00:41:18.430
beam and the light force
ignores that the light force

00:41:18.430 --> 00:41:20.360
is resonant, that the
light force depends

00:41:20.360 --> 00:41:21.401
on polarization and such.

00:41:31.170 --> 00:41:34.590
So the solution
is the divergence

00:41:34.590 --> 00:41:39.390
of-- If the c parameter
is spatially dependent,

00:41:39.390 --> 00:41:43.260
then we can have a divergence,
and then, we can do trapping.

00:41:43.260 --> 00:41:49.250
And it was actually Dave
Pritchard in '85 or in '86

00:41:49.250 --> 00:41:51.820
who wrote a really
influential paper.

00:41:51.820 --> 00:41:55.850
He said the Optical Earnshaw
theorem can be circumvented.

00:41:55.850 --> 00:41:58.800
We can have a spatially
dependent factor,

00:41:58.800 --> 00:42:01.840
and what can be spatially
dependent is saturation.

00:42:01.840 --> 00:42:05.230
If you focus a laser beam,
you have a spatially varying

00:42:05.230 --> 00:42:06.850
saturation parameter.

00:42:06.850 --> 00:42:08.700
There can be some
optical pumping.

00:42:08.700 --> 00:42:11.710
There can be light--

00:42:11.710 --> 00:42:13.900
So he discussed
several possibilities

00:42:13.900 --> 00:42:17.750
how the Optical Earnshaw
theorem was circumvented.

00:42:17.750 --> 00:42:21.010
At this point in 1986,
he didn't realize

00:42:21.010 --> 00:42:24.350
that it can be done with
a magnetic field gradient.

00:42:24.350 --> 00:42:28.570
When he talked about possible
ways of circumventing

00:42:28.570 --> 00:42:32.630
the Optical Earnshaw theorem,
Jean Dalibard, who many of who

00:42:32.630 --> 00:42:34.830
know, who's a famous
researcher in our field,

00:42:34.830 --> 00:42:37.530
had the idea that applying
a magnetic field gradient

00:42:37.530 --> 00:42:38.730
could work.

00:42:38.730 --> 00:42:40.760
But nobody thought,
at this time,

00:42:40.760 --> 00:42:43.110
that it would work
in three dimensions,

00:42:43.110 --> 00:42:45.040
so the fact that it
works in three dimensions

00:42:45.040 --> 00:42:47.180
is almost a miracle.

00:42:47.180 --> 00:42:51.190
So when the idea was born,
all those schemes, and also

00:42:51.190 --> 00:42:54.710
the original idea of applying
a magnetic field gradient,

00:42:54.710 --> 00:42:57.970
were conceived as
one dimension scheme.

00:42:57.970 --> 00:43:00.950
Most of the schemes can
not be easily generalized

00:43:00.950 --> 00:43:05.100
to three dimension,
but the MOT scheme

00:43:05.100 --> 00:43:08.830
works as well in three dimension
as it works in one dimension.

00:43:08.830 --> 00:43:12.370
Anyway, so this is
sort of the background.

00:43:12.370 --> 00:43:17.170
Since I was a postdoc
when there were only two

00:43:17.170 --> 00:43:20.400
or three groups who were
operating a magneto-optic trap,

00:43:20.400 --> 00:43:22.140
I put together,
with my own hands,

00:43:22.140 --> 00:43:24.525
the first magneto-optic trap
which was ever used at MIT.

00:43:24.525 --> 00:43:28.480
I mean, it's ancient
history, so I

00:43:28.480 --> 00:43:31.500
wanted to share a little
bit this history to you.

00:43:31.500 --> 00:43:33.890
But let me now simply
describe to you

00:43:33.890 --> 00:43:35.710
how the magneto-optic
trap works.

00:43:40.060 --> 00:43:45.524
Let me describe it
for an atom which

00:43:45.524 --> 00:43:46.690
we are not using in the lab.

00:43:46.690 --> 00:43:49.030
We all usually use atoms which
have hyperfine structure.

00:43:49.030 --> 00:43:51.700
But let me just for
pedagogical simplicity

00:43:51.700 --> 00:43:55.930
assume that we have an atom
which has an s to p transition,

00:43:55.930 --> 00:44:01.390
and in the p transition,
we have the three different

00:44:01.390 --> 00:44:02.980
magnetic [? quantum ?] numbers.

00:44:02.980 --> 00:44:05.610
So it's a simplified model.

00:44:05.610 --> 00:44:08.990
And what we're
doing right now is

00:44:08.990 --> 00:44:13.650
we are applying molasses, two
beams which act as molasses,

00:44:13.650 --> 00:44:15.470
but there is one difference now.

00:44:15.470 --> 00:44:17.750
They have different
polarizations, sigma plus

00:44:17.750 --> 00:44:21.080
and sigma minus,
and in addition, we

00:44:21.080 --> 00:44:24.530
apply a linear magnetic
field gradient.

00:44:24.530 --> 00:44:26.670
So what happens now
is the following.

00:44:26.670 --> 00:44:28.820
The linear magnetic
field gradient

00:44:28.820 --> 00:44:32.030
does Zeeman shifts in
the opposite direction

00:44:32.030 --> 00:44:35.400
to the n plus 1 and
n minus 1 level.

00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:40.290
Now, the transition to m minus
1 is done by sigma plus light.

00:44:40.290 --> 00:44:44.470
The transition to m plus 1
is done by sigma minus light.

00:44:44.470 --> 00:44:48.730
So what happens now
is if you have an atom

00:44:48.730 --> 00:44:52.050
and it moves away
from the origin,

00:44:52.050 --> 00:44:55.350
it will eventually come
closer and closer in resonance

00:44:55.350 --> 00:44:58.410
with the sigma plus light,
but the sigma plus light

00:44:58.410 --> 00:45:02.550
comes from the left side so
the atom will be pushed back.

00:45:02.550 --> 00:45:06.580
If the atom moves out hear, it
moves further and further away,

00:45:06.580 --> 00:45:08.670
in resonance, from
the sigma plus light,

00:45:08.670 --> 00:45:11.760
but it moves now, in resonance,
over the sigma minus light,

00:45:11.760 --> 00:45:15.920
and the sigma minus light
is pushing the atoms back.

00:45:15.920 --> 00:45:21.230
So this geometry has an inward
force from both directions

00:45:21.230 --> 00:45:23.298
and therefore, works as a trap.

00:45:31.914 --> 00:45:33.580
So let me now describe
it mathematically

00:45:33.580 --> 00:45:36.400
which is very, very simple.

00:45:36.400 --> 00:45:39.940
What we have to do is we
just have, like in molasses,

00:45:39.940 --> 00:45:43.090
two laser beams two
times the expression

00:45:43.090 --> 00:45:44.960
for the spontaneous light force.

00:45:44.960 --> 00:45:48.860
And you'll remember we
got the molasses equation

00:45:48.860 --> 00:45:51.820
by taking the two laser beams
and putting in the Doppler

00:45:51.820 --> 00:45:54.710
shift which is a
velocity dependent shift.

00:45:54.710 --> 00:45:58.580
Well, all we have to do is,
for those two laser beams,

00:45:58.580 --> 00:46:03.260
we have to put now a spatially
dependent Zeeman shift which

00:46:03.260 --> 00:46:06.960
varies linearly with position.

00:46:06.960 --> 00:46:14.620
So therefore, all we have to
do is we sum up the total force

00:46:14.620 --> 00:46:16.720
as the spontaneous
force for the right

00:46:16.720 --> 00:46:19.350
and for the left laser
beam, and in addition

00:46:19.350 --> 00:46:24.570
to the molasses effect, we put
now in the spatial dependence.

00:46:24.570 --> 00:46:26.840
So we don't have to
do the math again.

00:46:26.840 --> 00:46:29.840
We did already a
Taylor expansion in v,

00:46:29.840 --> 00:46:31.565
but let's now just
do a Taylor expansion

00:46:31.565 --> 00:46:33.390
in the blue expression.

00:46:33.390 --> 00:46:36.830
And then, we find that there
is a linearly restoring force

00:46:36.830 --> 00:46:42.360
both in velocity space and
in configuration space which

00:46:42.360 --> 00:46:45.180
actually tells you
something interesting.

00:46:45.180 --> 00:46:50.410
The more friction you have, the
larger is the restoring force.

00:46:50.410 --> 00:46:54.670
So the trapping and the
cooling are really connected,

00:46:54.670 --> 00:47:00.730
at least in the simple model
of the spontaneous light force.

00:47:00.730 --> 00:47:04.800
OK, so if we have
this kind of force,

00:47:04.800 --> 00:47:09.130
a linear force in velocity,
a linear force in position,

00:47:09.130 --> 00:47:11.380
this is the equation of
motion of a damped harmonic

00:47:11.380 --> 00:47:12.470
oscillator.

00:47:12.470 --> 00:47:15.600
You have a spatial
force constant, k,

00:47:15.600 --> 00:47:18.440
this linear force which
is linear in displacement.

00:47:18.440 --> 00:47:22.330
So this is a damped
harmonic oscillator.

00:47:22.330 --> 00:47:24.560
Usually, you don't
see atoms sloshing

00:47:24.560 --> 00:47:27.820
in your magneto-optic trap
like in an harmonic oscillator

00:47:27.820 --> 00:47:30.720
because if you look through
the [? typical ?] numbers

00:47:30.720 --> 00:47:32.830
and by just doing
the Taylor expansion

00:47:32.830 --> 00:47:35.040
of the spontaneous light
force, you can immediately

00:47:35.040 --> 00:47:38.540
get an alluded expressions
for those numbers.

00:47:38.540 --> 00:47:41.270
In almost all cases,
the harmonic oscillator

00:47:41.270 --> 00:47:42.040
is overdamped.

00:47:45.240 --> 00:47:48.050
So that's how the
magneto-optic trap works.

00:47:54.510 --> 00:48:00.820
However, the magneto-optic
trap is not so simple.

00:48:00.820 --> 00:48:02.520
I would actually
say nobody fully

00:48:02.520 --> 00:48:04.600
understands the
magneto-optic trap

00:48:04.600 --> 00:48:07.230
because we have
multi-level structure.

00:48:07.230 --> 00:48:09.510
We don't have just
one count level.

00:48:09.510 --> 00:48:17.360
A sodium and a
rubidium atom has--

00:48:17.360 --> 00:48:21.450
f equals one and f equals two--
has eight different hyperfine

00:48:21.450 --> 00:48:22.220
levels.

00:48:22.220 --> 00:48:25.650
So there is not one level
and we can excite the atoms.

00:48:25.650 --> 00:48:27.260
There are eight
different levels.

00:48:27.260 --> 00:48:30.290
And those laser beams to optical
pumping among those eight

00:48:30.290 --> 00:48:32.640
levels, and you have to
solve a rate equation

00:48:32.640 --> 00:48:34.560
for eight different levels.

00:48:34.560 --> 00:48:37.280
And the amazing thing
is it still works.

00:48:37.280 --> 00:48:39.470
It still works
pretty much, at least

00:48:39.470 --> 00:48:43.060
qualitatively, as well as
I just described to you.

00:48:43.060 --> 00:48:47.160
So it's a combination of optical
pumping and Zeeman shifts.

00:48:47.160 --> 00:48:49.640
It even works better
than advertised

00:48:49.640 --> 00:48:52.520
because as I will tell
you in the next few weeks,

00:48:52.520 --> 00:48:55.170
you can reach
temperatures-- Because

00:48:55.170 --> 00:48:57.260
of the multi-level
structure, you

00:48:57.260 --> 00:49:01.030
reach temperatures which are
much colder than the Doppler

00:49:01.030 --> 00:49:02.080
limit.

00:49:02.080 --> 00:49:03.890
It's called polarization
gradient cooling.

00:49:03.890 --> 00:49:05.740
It's just if you
have laser beams

00:49:05.740 --> 00:49:07.573
and you have atoms with
hyperfine structure,

00:49:07.573 --> 00:49:09.620
they are colder than
the Doppler limit.

00:49:09.620 --> 00:49:12.270
First, nobody understood
it, and then, Bill Phillips

00:49:12.270 --> 00:49:14.180
figured it out.

00:49:14.180 --> 00:49:17.450
And that he figured
out why atoms

00:49:17.450 --> 00:49:24.380
get colder that
was the main point

00:49:24.380 --> 00:49:25.840
emphasized by the
Nobel Committee

00:49:25.840 --> 00:49:27.990
when he got the Nobel
Prize for laser cooling.

00:49:27.990 --> 00:49:30.510
Of course, he had already
invented Zeeman slowing before,

00:49:30.510 --> 00:49:33.330
so he had a few other
things under his belt.

00:49:33.330 --> 00:49:36.820
But anyway, the fact
that the MOT works

00:49:36.820 --> 00:49:40.220
even better than advertised
is another miracle,

00:49:40.220 --> 00:49:43.200
and this is related to
the hyperfine structure.

00:49:43.200 --> 00:49:50.490
And finally, the fact that
you can simply extended it

00:49:50.490 --> 00:49:54.570
to three dimension, is-- I said
the first, the second --maybe

00:49:54.570 --> 00:49:55.680
the third miracle.

00:49:55.680 --> 00:49:57.030
It also works.

00:49:57.030 --> 00:49:59.110
Because when you
look at the field

00:49:59.110 --> 00:50:04.390
of two coils, a so-called
Anti-Helmholtz field,

00:50:04.390 --> 00:50:11.110
