00:50:12.250 --> 00:50:14.650
This is a much more
complicated magnetic field.

00:50:14.650 --> 00:50:16.720
It goes outward
here, outward here,

00:50:16.720 --> 00:50:21.090
but in between the quadrupolar
field, it sort of curves.

00:50:21.090 --> 00:50:25.060
There are some directions
where the magnetic field is not

00:50:25.060 --> 00:50:28.404
radial, and you would say, hey,
the one dimensional scheme is

00:50:28.404 --> 00:50:29.320
[INAUDIBLE] [? set. ?]

00:50:32.290 --> 00:50:34.710
Actually, before the
magneto-optic trap

00:50:34.710 --> 00:50:36.590
was demonstrated, Dave
Pritchard's student,

00:50:36.590 --> 00:50:38.650
Eric [? Rob ?] did
calculations what

00:50:38.650 --> 00:50:42.770
happens in these
diagonal directions which

00:50:42.770 --> 00:50:45.630
have no resemblance to
the one dimension scheme.

00:50:45.630 --> 00:50:47.992
The solution is in
those directions,

00:50:47.992 --> 00:50:49.700
the trapping form is
a little bit weaker,

00:50:49.700 --> 00:50:53.200
but the big picture
