01:01:33.230 --> 01:01:35.450
And after some
approximations, exactly

01:01:35.450 --> 01:01:38.390
solve what the atom does
with one laser beam.

01:01:41.890 --> 01:01:45.530
So the laser beam is described
by the standard Hamiltonian

01:01:45.530 --> 01:01:46.880
for single mode light.

01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:51.150
The atom is described by, well,
excitation energy omega 0.

01:01:51.150 --> 01:01:53.860
And b is the excited state.

01:01:53.860 --> 01:01:57.990
So if you don't have any
light atom interaction,

01:01:57.990 --> 01:02:02.740
